postcontent:
I have an excellent condition S&W 686-4, it's an older model made prior to the introduction of S&W's lawyer-safties that can lock up during firing.  It doesn't have that "feature".  It also has the firing pin mounted on the hammer.  Full stainless steel 4 inch barrel with full underlug, red ramp sight, stainless L-Frame (more durable than model 19s or 66s), I replaced the grips with Nills.  For those unaware, Nills are German made grips made from the finest walnut in the world, perfectly fit and finished... they will make Hogue grips blush, there is simply no higher quality grip on the market.  The Nills make your hand sit higher on the grip, lowering the bore axis and properly positioning your finger on the trigger.  Speaking of the trigger, this has a trigger job from the Performance center, it is the finest trigger on a revolver I've ever shot, period.  The gun has been fired, but cleaned and maintained well.  With the trigger, the gun is easily one of my best shooters and it's an absolute riot at the range.  I will include a couple of speed loaders to get you going with the gun.  

Asking price is 875$ even, FIRM on that given the amount of work and cost of the grips on the pistol.  Trust me, it's worth that price and then some.  I'm pearing down my pistol collection tho, and this one's strickly a range pistol for me, not a CCW piece, so it's on the chopping block.  You COULD CCW this if you wanted, it's not a huge pistol, but I'd just like more capacity.  

NO TRADES.  You'll need a pistol purchase permit or a CCW to buy the gun in NC.  I'm local around Apex, but willing to drive to Raleigh or Cary if you're interested in the gun.  I'm also willing to ship on your dime.  If you want the ultimate shooter's revolver and .357 magnum power, this is it.  It hits accurately and hits hard.
